## Context

- rb1-loss-pancancer-dependency-atlas: Launched project. Moved planning → development.
- Created 5 developer tasks (#762-#766) for Phases 1-5, following CDKN2A atlas methodology pattern.
- Phase 1 (#762): RB1-loss classifier (multi-modal: mutations, CN < 0.5, expression bottom quartile; CDK4/6i resistance positive control; CCNE1/TP53 co-alteration tracking)
- Phase 2 (#763): Candidate SL dependencies (CDK2, AURKA/B, CHK1, WEE1, CK2, TTK, FOXM1; CDK4/6 negative controls)
- Phase 3 (#764): Genome-wide screen (~18K genes, pathway enrichment, CDKN2A comparison)
- Phase 4 (#765): PRISM drug validation (CDK2i, Aurora, CHK1/WEE1i, platinum, PARPi)
- Phase 5 (#766): TCGA clinical integration (CDK2 inhibitor landscape, priority matrix)
- Next: Monitor developer progress on Phase 1. When dev tasks complete → create analyst tasks for interpretation. When analysis done → validation_scientist tasks.
